You are a senior Laravel engineer. Build an Airbnb-like property listing site using:
- Laravel (latest stable)
- Livewire (latest stable)
- Laravel default authentication scaffolding already installed (login/register/password reset)
- Testing framework: Pest

This app has:
1) PUBLIC “SHOWROOM” browsing of listings (no login button, no account UI for clients)
2) HIDDEN ADMIN PANEL accessible only by typing /login (no public links)
3) Admin manages listings (“units”), categories, media, pricing display options
4) Clients can request a “book a viewing” schedule using a calendar UI (no client login)
5) Pricing calculations for stays (nightly and monthly) with flexible display mode
6) Real-time notifications to admin when viewing request is submitted
7) Storage starts on local public disk but must be switchable to S3 by .env only

ABSOLUTE SECURITY REQUIREMENTS:
- Never expose API keys or secrets in client-side code (Blade, Livewire rendered HTML, JS).
- Store secrets only in .env and config files.
- For real-time notifications (Pusher/WebSockets/etc.), keep keys server-side; do not embed secrets in JS. Use backend broadcasting config properly.
- For storage (S3/Cloudinary), use backend-controlled uploads or signed upload URLs; never ship credentials to the browser.
- Do not commit .env. Do not log secrets.

========================================================
A) PUBLIC SHOWROOM REQUIREMENTS (NO LOGIN UI)
========================================================
Routes:
- GET / : listings showroom
- GET /units/{unit:slug_or_public_id} : listing detail page (or Livewire modal)

Public Showroom features:
- Search bar (by unit name/location keyword)
- Category filter chips (default categories seedable; admin can CRUD)
- Unit cards show:
  - Cover image
  - Name/title
  - Category
  - Price display (depends on unit setting: per night or per month) with PHP currency formatting (₱)
  - Availability badge (Available / Unavailable)
- Unit detail page shows:
  - Image slideshow/gallery
  - Description
  - Pricing section:
     - Display price in the unit’s chosen display mode (nightly or monthly)
     - Price estimator widget:
        - user selects check-in/check-out dates
        - show computed nights + total price
        - if stay length qualifies for monthly pricing, apply monthly price rule as configured
  - “Request a Viewing” section:
     - calendar date picker + time slot selector
     - submits a viewing request (no client login)
     - shows success message with requested date/time

IMPORTANT:
- Public pages MUST NOT contain any login/register buttons or admin links.
- Admin access is only via /login typed in the browser.

========================================================
B) ADMIN PANEL REQUIREMENTS
========================================================
Admin routes (auth protected):
- /admin (dashboard)
- /admin/units (index/search/filter)
- /admin/units/create
- /admin/units/{unit}/edit
- /admin/categories (CRUD)
- /admin/viewing-requests (manage scheduled viewings)
- /admin/logs (audit logs)

Admin Dashboard UI sections (functional requirements):
- KPIs: total units, available, unavailable, viewing requests upcoming, requests this week
- Quick Actions: Add unit, Manage categories, View viewing requests
- Recent Activity: last 10 log entries
- Upcoming Viewings: next 10 scheduled viewing requests

Admin Units management:
Unit fields:
- name/title (required)
- category_id (required)
- location (string nullable)
- description (text nullable)
- status (AVAILABLE/UNAVAILABLE) default AVAILABLE
- pricing:
  - nightly_price_php (nullable integer)
  - monthly_price_php (nullable integer)
  - price_display_mode enum: NIGHT or MONTH (controls what the public card primarily shows)
  - allow_estimator boolean default true
- media: multiple images with sort_order
- soft deletes enabled
- created_by / updated_by tracked (optional but recommended)

Admin can:
- create/edit/soft-delete/restore units
- upload images, remove images, reorder images
- set availability status explicitly (no ambiguous toggles; use explicit actions)
- set pricing display mode (per night or per month)
- configure whether estimator uses nightly only, monthly only, or hybrid rule (see Pricing Rules)

Admin Categories management:
- Seed default categories (e.g., Condo, House, Studio, Room, Villa) and allow CRUD.
- Prevent deletion if category has units.

Admin Viewing Requests:
- List requests with filters:
  - date range, unit, status (PENDING/CONFIRMED/CANCELLED)
- Ability to confirm/cancel requests
- Show details: requester name, phone/email, requested datetime, unit, notes

========================================================
C) CALENDAR + VIEWING REQUESTS (NO CLIENT LOGIN)
========================================================
Create ViewingRequest flow:
Public submits:
- unit_id
- requested_start_at (datetime)
- requested_end_at (datetime optional or fixed duration)
- requester_name
- requester_phone (optional)
- requester_email (optional)
- notes (optional)

Validation:
- requested_start_at must be in the future
- prevent overlaps for the same unit in CONFIRMED state (and optionally PENDING)
- rate-limit request submissions per IP

========================================================
D) PRICING ENGINE REQUIREMENTS
========================================================
Pricing display + calculation:
- Store nightly_price_php and monthly_price_php as integers (₱ whole pesos; no formatted strings in DB).
- Unit has price_display_mode:
   - NIGHT: cards show nightly price
   - MONTH: cards show monthly price

Estimator:
- Input check-in/out dates
- Compute number of nights
- Compute total using rule:
   1) If monthly_price_php exists AND stay length >= 30 nights:
       - months = floor(nights / 30)
       - remainder = nights % 30
       - total = months * monthly_price + remainder * nightly_price (if nightly exists) else prorate monthly/30 (define rule)
   2) Else:
       - total = nights * nightly_price

Define and implement a clear rule when nightly is missing but monthly exists:
- If nightly is null and monthly exists: nightly_rate = round(monthly_price / 30)
Same for missing monthly but nightly exists: monthly_display optional computed? No—only if stored.

Ensure currency formatting:
- Use PHP formatting for ₱ with thousand separators (en-PH).

========================================================
E) REAL-TIME NOTIFICATIONS TO ADMIN (VIEWING REQUESTS)
========================================================
Requirement:
- When a viewing request is created, notify admin in real time.

Implementation options:
- Laravel broadcasting events + WebSockets (Pusher-compatible) OR Laravel WebSockets (self-hosted).
- Use Notification system:
   - ViewingRequested notification sent to admins (users with is_admin)
- Admin UI:
   - Notification bell badge count
   - “Recent notifications” dropdown
   - Viewing Requests page highlights new requests

SECURITY:
- Do not expose broadcasting secrets client-side.
- Use proper broadcasting config with public key only if required; keep secrets server-side.

========================================================
F) STORAGE REQUIREMENTS (LOCAL DEV/DEMO + S3 READY)
========================================================
- Default FILESYSTEM_DISK=public in .env
- Store only relative paths in DB: units/{unit_id}/{filename}.jpg
- Render URLs via Storage::url($path)
- Never store full URLs in DB
- Document `php artisan storage:link` in README
- Switching to S3 must only require .env change (FILESYSTEM_DISK=s3 + creds)

========================================================
G) DATABASE / MODELS (MANDATORY)
========================================================
Tables:
1) categories: id, name unique, timestamps
2) units:
   - id, public_id (ULID) unique indexed
   - category_id fk indexed
   - name indexed
   - slug (optional unique) OR use public_id for routing
   - location nullable
   - description nullable
   - status AVAILABLE/UNAVAILABLE indexed
   - nightly_price_php nullable
   - monthly_price_php nullable
   - price_display_mode NIGHT/MONTH
   - allow_estimator boolean
   - created_by, updated_by nullable indexed
   - timestamps, softDeletes
3) unit_images:
   - id, unit_id fk indexed, path (relative), sort_order, timestamps
4) viewing_requests:
   - id, unit_id fk indexed
   - requester_name, requester_email nullable, requester_phone nullable
   - requested_start_at indexed
   - requested_end_at nullable
   - status PENDING/CONFIRMED/CANCELLED indexed
   - notes nullable
   - created_at, updated_at
5) audit_logs (or unit_inventory_logs):
   - id, unit_id nullable, user_id nullable
   - action (CREATE/UPDATE/SET_AVAILABLE/SET_UNAVAILABLE/IMAGE_ADD/IMAGE_REMOVE/VIEWING_REQUEST_CREATED/VIEWING_REQUEST_CONFIRMED/...)
   - changes JSON nullable
   - ip_address/user_agent nullable
   - created_at

Relationships:
- Category hasMany Units
- Unit belongsTo Category
- Unit hasMany UnitImages ordered by sort_order
- Unit hasMany ViewingRequests
- ViewingRequest belongsTo Unit
- AuditLog belongsTo Unit and User

========================================================
H) AUTHORIZATION
========================================================
- Add users.is_admin boolean (or role)
- Admin routes: middleware(['auth','verified','admin'])
- Non-admin authenticated users get 403
- Public routes never allow mutation endpoints

========================================================
I) LIVEWIRE COMPONENTS (SUGGESTED)
========================================================
Public:
- ShowroomIndex (search + category filters + units grid)
- UnitShow (detail + gallery + estimator + viewing request form)

Admin:
- AdminDashboard
- AdminUnitsIndex
- AdminUnitForm
- AdminCategories
- AdminViewingRequests
- AdminLogs
- AdminNotificationsBell (optional)

========================================================
J) TESTING (PEST)
========================================================
Write Pest tests for:
- Public showroom returns 200
- No public login link exists on public pages (assert notContains '/login' link)
- Admin routes redirect guest to login
- Non-admin user gets 403 on /admin
- Admin can CRUD categories and units
- Storage saves relative image paths only
- Viewing request validation (future date required)
- Viewing request creates audit log and triggers notification (fake notifications)
- Pricing calculator:
  - nightly only
  - monthly only (derive nightly from monthly/30)
  - hybrid months + remainder
- Concurrency safety for availability updates (transaction + lockForUpdate) if implemented

========================================================
K) README
========================================================
Document:
- Setup, migrate, seed
- storage:link
- Admin access: type /login then /admin
- Real-time notifications setup notes (env vars)
- Security warning: never expose API keys client-side; backend-only patterns
Deliver clean code, passing tests, minimal but production-oriented.
